      <section class="method-section">
        <div class="container method-prose">
          <h2 data-i18n="method-what-title">What this is</h2>
          <p data-i18n="method-what-body">
            BetterCamNorte is an independent, citizen-led transparency project. It is not an
            official website of the Provincial Government of Camarines Norte. Our one job is to help
            citizens trace where Camarines Norte's public money goes.
          </p>

          <h2 data-i18n="method-rule-title">The rule every dataset must pass</h2>
          <p data-i18n="method-rule-body">
            Structured figure datasets covered by our provenance check must carry a source, a source
            link, and an as-of date or the build fails. Other site content is reviewed separately
            and is not automatically covered by that check. Figures whose provenance we cannot
            establish are unpublished, not estimated.
          </p>

          <h2 data-i18n="method-projects-title">Public projects (DPWH)</h2>
          <p>
            <span data-i18n="method-projects-source-before">Project data comes from the</span>
            <a
              href="https://transparency.dpwh.gov.ph/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-i18n="method-dpwh-link"
              >DPWH Transparency Portal</a
            ><span data-i18n="method-projects-source-after"
              >, refreshed each time the site is built. We scan the portal's national records and
              keep the contracts that match Camarines Norte. Live totals are shown on the</span
            >
            <a href="../projects/" data-i18n="method-projects-link">Projects page</a
            ><span data-i18n="method-projects-link-after"> so the two pages cannot disagree.</span>
          </p>
          <p data-i18n="method-projects-counting">
            Headline figures cover contracts tagged to the Camarines Norte District Engineering
            Office (DEO). Contracts that only mention Camarines Norte under the broader Region V tag
            are counted separately, because attributing them to the province would overstate local
            spending.
          </p>

          <h2 data-i18n="method-honest-title">Honest states</h2>
          <p>
            <span data-i18n="method-honest-before-blgf"
              >We show gaps rather than hide them. A contract with no disclosed contractor reads
              "Not stated in source"; a contract with no published budget shows a dash, not a
              guessed amount. The provincial fiscal summary is currently awaiting figures from
              the</span
            >
            <a
              href="https://blgf.gov.ph/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              data-i18n="method-blgf-link"
              >BLGF</a
            ><span data-i18n="method-honest-after-blgf"
              >, so the section says so plainly instead of showing draft numbers as final.</span
            >
          </p>

          <h2 data-i18n="method-freshness-title">Freshness</h2>
          <p data-i18n="method-freshness-body">
            DPWH project data is re-pulled on every build. Each figure carries its own as-of date,
            so you can see how current it is rather than assuming it's live. Datasets still awaiting
            an official source are labelled with when they were last checked.
          </p>

          <h2 data-i18n="method-corrections-title">Found a mistake? Tell us.</h2>
          <p data-i18n="method-corrections-body">
            Corrections are a feature, not an embarrassment. If a figure looks wrong, point us at
            the right source and we'll fix it:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <span data-i18n="method-corrections-issue">Open an issue:</span>
              <a
                href="https://github.com/Exc1D/better-camnorte/issues/new"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                >github.com/Exc1D/better-camnorte/issues</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <span data-i18n="method-corrections-email">Or email</span>
              <a href="mailto:volunteer@bettercamnorte.org">volunteer@bettercamnorte.org</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p data-i18n="method-corrections-source">
            Please include a link to the official source so we can verify and cite it.
          </p>
        </div>
